Package au.edu.anu.twcore.ecosystem.runtime

Interface DynamicSystem

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CategorizedComponent
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArenaComponent, GroupComponent, HierarchicalComponent, LifeCycleComponent, SystemComponent
    public interface DynamicSystem
    Objects that have state variables that can be modified along time should implement this interface.

    3Worlds: component threeWorlds

    Author:
    Jacques Gignoux - 27 sept. 2012 updated 20/2/2017

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      TwData currentState()
      returns the current (t) state variables of this system
      void extrapolateState​(long time)
      extrapolate data to a hypothetical next state at a given time based on the past evolution of states, recorded within this object
      void interpolateState​(long time)
      interpolate a state between two already computed states given an intermediate time.
      TwData nextState()
      returns the future (t+1) state variables of this system
      TwData previousState()
      returns the previous (t-1) state variables of this system
      TwData previousState​(int stepsBack)
      returns the previous (t-stepsBack) state variables of this system
      TwData state​(int stepIndex)
      returns a state with -1 = next, 0 = current, 1 = past[0], 2 = past[1], etc
      void stepBackward()
      goes back in time one step

      goes back in time nSteps steps
